values: "So tell me, what do the people think of Holland in America?" ::pause:: "Well, we don't, really." "What? How do you mean?" "We have opinions about the Germans, and the French, and the British, but we don't really talk about the Netherlands much." "But... Amsterdam, surely-" "Oh, yeah, we've heard all about Amsterdam, but I'm guessing most of us think it's in Denmark." ::sad face::

This is the best and highest use of the internet. 

<lj-embed id="1" />
(work safe if drunken monkeys and resulting shrieks of delight are acceptable at your place of business)

Right now on campus there is a rousing chant in the "WHAT DO WE WANT? _______!  WHEN DO WE WANT IT? ___________!" format.  From the building I'm in, though, I can only hear the guy with the megaphone posing the questions, not the angry mob replying.  it's very disconcerting.

I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT THEY WANT.
